article.headline: Maine 79, St. Francis, N.Y. 60
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Kevin Reed scored 19 of his 30 points in the first half and Maine beat St. Francis of New York 79-60 Saturday. Reed made eight of 11 3-pointers, and Jon Sheets, Junior Bernal and Phil Tchekane-Bofia had 11 points apiece for the Black Bears (1-3). Robert Hines had 18 points and Jamaal Womack finished with 11 for the Terriers (0-4). John Godden's three point play got St. Francis within two with 11:05 left in the first half but Reed scored 11 points in a 21-6 run that put the Black Bears up 35-22 with 4:54 left. Maine led 39-30 at halftime.
